President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of South Carolina due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is now available for emergency protective measures and direct federal assistance. Gracia B. Szczech has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.